(5, 54, 2, 'Drowzee', 'Pokémon Power : Long-Distance Hypnosis\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. If tails, your Active Pokémon is now Asleep. This power can''t be used if Drowzee is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[P][C] Nightmare : 10\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.'),
(5, 55, 2, 'Eevee', '[C] Tackle : 10\r\n\r\n[C][C] Sand-attack : 10\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent''s next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.'),
