(8, 91, 2, 'Bill''s Teleporter', 'Flip a coin. If heads, draw 4 cards.'),
(8, 92, 2, 'Card-Flip Game', 'Choose 1 of your opponent''s face-down Prizes. Guess whether it is an Energy card, a Trainer card, or a Pokémon (Basic or Evolution) card. Flip the card face up (and leave it face up). If you guessed right, draw 2 cards.'),
(8, 93, 2, 'Gold Berry', 'Attach Gold Berry to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn''t have a Pokémon Tool attached to it.\r\n\r\nAt any time between turns, if there are at least 4 damage counters of the Pokémon Gold Berry is attached to, you may remove 4 of them and discard Gold Berry. At the start of each turn, if there are at least 4 damage counters on the Pokémon Gold Berry is attached to, remove 4 of them and discard Gold Berry.'),
(8, 94, 2, 'Miracle Berry', 'Attach Miracle Berry to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn''t have a Pokémon Tool attached to it.\r\n\r\nAt any time between turns, if the Pokémon Miracle Berry is attached to is Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned, you may remove all those effects from that Pokémon and discard Miracle Berry. At the start of each turn, if the Pokémon Miracle Berry is attached to is Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned, remove all of those effects from that Pokémon and discard Miracle Berry.'),
(8, 95, 2, 'New Pokédex', 'Shuffle your deck. Then, look at up to 5 cards from the top of your deck and rearrange them as you like.'),
(8, 96, 2, 'Professor Elm', 'Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 7 cards. You can''t play any more Trainer cards this turn.'),
(8, 97, 2, 'Sprout Tower', 'All damage done by [C] Pokémon''s attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).'),
(8, 98, 2, 'Super Scoop Up', 'Flip a coin. If heads, return 1 of your Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your hand.'),
(8, 99, 2, 'Berry', 'At any time between turns, if there are at least 2 damage counters on the Pokémon Berry is attached to, you may remove 2 of them and discard Berry. At the start of each turn, if there are at least 2 damage counters on the Pokémon Berry is attached to, remove 2 of them and discard Berry.'),
(8, 100, 2, 'Double Gust', 'If you have any Benched Pokémon, your opponent chooses 1 of them and switches it with your Active Pokémon. Then, if your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, choose 1 of them and switch it with his or her Active Pokémon.'),
(8, 101, 2, 'Moo-Moo Milk', 'Choose 1 of your Pokémon. Flip 2 coins. Remove 2 damage counters times the number of heads from that Pokémon. If the Pokémon has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.'),
(8, 102, 2, 'Pokémon March', 'Your opponent may search his or her deck for 1 Basic Pokémon card and put it onto his or her Bench. Then, you may search your deck for 1 Basic Pokémon card and put it onto your Bench. Then, each player shuffles his or her deck. (A player can''t do any of this if his or her Bench is full.)'),
(8, 103, 2, 'Super Rod', 'Flip a coin. If heads, put an Evolution card from your discard pile, if any, into your hand. If tails, put a Basic Pokémon card from your discard pile, if any, into your hand.'),
(8, 104, 2, 'Darkness Energy', 'If the Pokémon Darkness Energy is attached to damages the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), the attack does 10 more damage to the Defending Pokémon. At the end of every turn, put 1 damage counter on the Pokémon Darkness Energy is attached to, unless it''s [D] or has Dark in its name.\r\n\r\nDarkness Energy provides [D] Energy. (Doesn''t count as a basic Energy card.)'),
(8, 105, 2, 'Recycle Energy', 'Recycle Energy provides [C] Energy. (Doesn''t count as a basic Energy card.)\r\n\r\nIf this card is put into your discard pile from play, return it to your hand.'),
