(13, 137, 2, 'Bill''s Maintenance', 'You can only play one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.\r\n\r\nIf you have any cards in your hand, shuffle 1 of them into your deck, then draw 3 cards.'),
(13, 138, 2, 'Copycat', 'You can only play one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.\r\n\r\nShuffle your hand into your deck. Then, count the number of cards in your opponent''s hand and draw that many cards.'),
(13, 139, 2, 'Dual Ball', 'Flip 2 coins. For each heads, search your deck for a Basic Pokémon card other than a Baby Pokémon card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.'),
(13, 140, 2, 'Energy Removal 2', 'Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 Energy card attached to 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon and discard it.'),
(13, 141, 2, 'Energy Restore', 'Flip 3 coins. For each heads, put a Basic Energy card from your discard pile into your hand. If you don''t have that many basic Energy cards in your discard pile, put all of them into your hand.'),
(13, 142, 2, 'Mary''s Impulse', 'You can only play one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.\r\n\r\nFlip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, draw 2 cards.'),
(13, 143, 2, 'Master Ball', 'Look at 7 cards from the top of your deck. You may choose a Basic Pokémon or Evolution card from those cards, show it your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle the rest into your deck.'),
(13, 144, 2, 'Multi Technical Machine 01', 'Attach this card to 1 of your Pokémon in play. That Pokémon may use this card''s attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Multi Technical Machine 01.\r\n\r\n[C] Paralyzing Gaze :\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.'),
(13, 145, 2, 'Pokémon Nurse', 'You can only play one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.\r\n\r\nRemove all damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon. Then discard all Energy cards attached to it, if any.'),
(13, 146, 2, 'Pokémon Reversal', 'Choose 1 of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon. Flip a coin. If heads, switch that Pokémon with the Defending Pokémon.'),
(13, 147, 2, 'Power Charge', 'Flip a coin. If heads, shuffle 2 Energy cards from your discard pile into your deck (1 if you have only 1).'),
(13, 148, 2, 'Professor Elm''s Training Method', 'You can only play one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.\r\n\r\nSearch your deck for an Evolution card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.'),
(13, 149, 2, 'Professor Oak''s Research', 'You can only play one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.\r\n\r\nShuffle your hand into your deck, then draw 5 cards.'),
(13, 150, 2, 'Strength Charm', 'Attach a Pokémon Tool to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn''t already have a Pokémon Tool attached to it.\r\n\r\nWhenever an attack from the Pokémon that Strength Charm is attached to does damage (after applying Weakness and Resistance), the attack does 10 more damage. At the end of your turn in which this happens, discard Strength Charm.'),
(13, 151, 2, 'Super Scoop Up', 'Flip a coin. If heads, return 1 of your Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your hand.'),
(13, 152, 2, 'Warp Point', 'Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon, if any; then you switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon, if any.'),
(13, 153, 2, 'Energy Search', 'Search your deck for a basic Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.'),
(13, 154, 2, 'Full Heal', 'Remove all Special Conditions from your Active Pokémon.'),
(13, 155, 2, 'Moo-Moo Milk', 'Choose 1 of your Pokémon. Flip 2 coins. Remove 2 damage counters times the number of heads from that Pokémon. If the Pokémon has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.'),
(13, 156, 2, 'Potion', 'Remove 2 damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon (1 if that Pokémon has only 1).'),
(13, 157, 2, 'Switch', 'Switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.'),
(13, 158, 2, 'Darkness Energy', 'If the Pokémon Darkness Energy is attached to does damage with an attack (after applying Weakness and Resistance), the attack does 10 more damage. At the end of every turn, put 1 damage counter on the Pokémon Darkness Energy is attached to, unless it''s [D] or has Dark in its name. Darkness Energy provides [D] Energy. (Doesn''t count as a basic Energy card.)'),
(13, 159, 2, 'Metal Energy', 'Damage done by attacks to the Pokémon Metal Energy is attached to is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance). If the Pokémon Metal Energy is attached to isn''t [M], whenever it damages a Pokémon by an attack, reduce that damage by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).\r\nMetal Energy provides [M] Energy. (Doesn''t count as a basic Energy cards.)'),
