(46, 85, 2, 'Black Belt', 'You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.\r\n\r\nYou may use this card only if you have more Prize cards left than your opponent. During this turn, each of your Active Pokémon''s attacks does 40 more damage to your opponent''s Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).'),
(46, 86, 2, 'Indigo Plateau', 'This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play. If another card with the same name is in play, you can''t play this card.\r\n\r\nEach Pokémon LEGEND in play (both yours and your opponent''s) gets +30 HP.'),
(46, 87, 2, 'Junk Arm', 'Discard 2 cards from you hand. Search your discard pile for a Trainer card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. You can''t choose Junk Arm with the effect of this card.'),
(46, 88, 2, 'Seeker', 'You may play only one Support card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.\r\n\r\nEach player returns 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon and all cards attached to it to his or her hand. (You return your Pokémon first.)'),
(46, 89, 2, 'Twins', 'You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.\r\n\r\nYou may use this card only if you have more Prize cards left than your opponent. Search your deck for any 2 cards and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.'),
(46, 90, 2, 'Rescue Energy', 'Rescue Energy provides 1 [C] Energy. IF the Pokémon this card is attached to is Knocked Out by damage from an attack, put that Pokémon back into your hand. (Discard all cards attached to that Pokémon.)'),
(46, 91, 2, 'Absol', 'Poké-Body : Eye of Disaster\r\nAs long as Absol is your Active Pokémon, whenever your opponent puts a Basic Pokémon from his or her hand onto his or her Bench, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[D][C] Vicious Claw : 70\r\nChoose 1 Pokémon from your hand and put it in the Lost Zone. (If you can''t put a Pokémon in the Lost Zone, this attack does nothing.)'),
(46, 92, 2, 'Celebi', 'Poké-Power : Forest Breath\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), if Celebi is your Active Pokémon, you may attach a [G] Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon. This power can''t be used if Celebi is affected by a Special Condition.\r\n\r\n[G][P][C] Time Circle : 30\r\nDuring your opponent''s next turn, prevent all damage done to Celebi by attacks from your opponent''s Stage 1 or Stage 2 Pokémon.'),
(46, 93, 2, 'Electrode', 'Poké-Power : Energymite\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. If you do, Electrode is Knocked Out. Look at the top 7 cards of your deck. Choose as many Energy cards as you like and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Discard the other cards. This power can''t be used if Electrode is affected by a Special Condition.\r\n\r\n[L][C] Gigashock : 30\r\nDoes 10 damage to 2 of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)'),
(46, 94, 2, 'Gengar', 'Poké-Body : Catastrophe\r\nAs long as Gengar is your Active Pokémon, if any of your opponent''s Pokémon would be Knocked Out, put that Pokémon in the Lost Zone instead of discarding. (Discard all cards attached to that Pokémon.)\r\n\r\n[P] Hurl into Darkness :\r\nLook at your opponent''s hand and choose a number of Pokémon you find there up to the number of Psychic Energy attached to Gengar. PUt the Pokémon you chose in the Lost Zone.\r\n\r\n[P][C] Cursed Drop :\r\nPut 4 damage counters on your opponent''s Pokémon in any way you like.'),
(46, 95, 2, 'Machamp', 'Poké-Power : Fighting Tag\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), if Machamp is on your Bench, you may move all [F] Energy attached to your Active Pokémon to Machamp. If you do, switch Machamp with your Active Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[F][C][C] Crushing Punch : 60\r\nDiscard a Special Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[F][F][C][C] Champ Buster : 100+\r\nDoes 100 damage plus 10 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it.'),
(46, 96, 2, 'Magnezone', 'Poké-Power : Magnetic Draw\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. This power can''t be used if Magnezone is affected by a Special Condition.\r\n\r\n[L][C] Lost Burn : 50×\r\nPut as many Energy cards attached to your Pokémon as you like in the Lost Zone. This attack does 50 damage times the number of Energy cards put in the Lost Zone in this way.'),
(46, 97, 2, 'Mew', 'Poké-Body : Lost Link\r\nMew can use the attacks of all Pokémon in the Lost Zone (both yours and your opponent''s). (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)\r\n\r\n[P] See Off :\r\nSearch your deck for 1 Pokémon and put it in the Lost Zone. Shuffle your deck afterward.'),
(46, 98, 2, 'Yanmega', 'Poké-Body : Insight\r\nIf you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, the attack cost of each of Yanmega''s attacks is 0.\r\n\r\n[G][C] Linear Attack :\r\nChoose 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)\r\n\r\n[G][G][C] Sonicboom : 70\r\nThis attack''s damage isn''t affected by Weakness or Resistance.'),
(46, 99, 2, 'Darkrai &amp; Cresselia LEGEND (Top)', '[D][D][C][C] Lost Crisis : 100\r\nChoose 2 Energy attached to Darkrai &amp; Cresselia LEGEND and put them in the Lost Zone. If any of your opponent''s Pokémon would be Knocked Out by damage from this attack, put that Pokémon and all cards attached to it in the Lost Zone instead of discarding it.\r\n\r\n[P] Moon''s Invite :\r\nMove as many damage counters on your opponent''s Pokémon as you like to any of your opponent''s other Pokémon in any way you like.'),
(46, 100, 2, 'Darkrai &amp; Cresselia LEGEND (Bottom)', '[D][D][C][C] Lost Crisis : 100\r\nChoose 2 Energy attached to Darkrai &amp; Cresselia LEGEND and put them in the Lost Zone. If any of your opponent''s Pokémon would be Knocked Out by damage from this attack, put that Pokémon and all cards attached to it in the Lost Zone instead of discarding it.\r\n\r\n[P] Moon''s Invite :\r\nMove as many damage counters on your opponent''s Pokémon as you like to any of your opponent''s other Pokémon in any way you like.'),
(46, 101, 2, 'Palkia &amp; Dialga LEGEND (Top)', '[W][C][C] Sudden Delete :\r\nChoose 1 of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon. Put that Pokémon and all cards attached to it back to your opponent''s hand.\r\n\r\n[M][M][C] Time Control :\r\nDiscard all [M] Energy attached to Palkia &amp; Dialga LEGEND. Add the top 2 cards of your opponent''s deck to his or her Prize cards.'),
(46, 102, 2, 'Palkia &amp; Dialga LEGEND (Bottom)', '[W][C][C] Sudden Delete :\r\nChoose 1 of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon. Put that Pokémon and all cards attached to it back to your opponent''s hand.\r\n\r\n[M][M][C] Time Control :\r\nDiscard all [M] Energy attached to Palkia &amp; Dialga LEGEND. Add the top 2 cards of your opponent''s deck to his or her Prize cards.');
