(10001, 65, 2, 'Graveler', '[F][F] Stone Barrage : 20×\r\nFlip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.\r\n\r\n[F][F][F] Earthquake : 50\r\nDoes 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)'),
(10001, 66, 2, 'Graveler', '[F][F][C] Boulder Smash : 30\r\nFlip 2 coins. For each heads, put 1 damage counter on 1 your opponent''s Benched Pokémon. '),
(10001, 67, 2, 'Golem', '[C][C] Rollout : 20\r\n\r\n[F][F][F] Rock Blast :	\r\nYou may discard up to 5 Fighting Energy cards attached to Golem. For each Fighting Energy you discarded, choose 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon and this attack does 20 damage to it. (You may choose the same Pokémon more than once.) Don’t apply Weakness or Resistance. '),
(10001, 68, 2, 'Onix', '[F] Bind : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[F][F] Rock Seal : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat during your opponent''s next turn. '),
(10001, 69, 2, 'Cubone', '[F] Bone Toss :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage to the Defending Pokémon. If tails, this attack does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)'),
(10001, 70, 2, 'Marowak', '[C] Look for Bone :\r\nIf this Pokémon doesn''t already have a Bone Counter on it, put a Bone Counter on it.\r\n\r\n[F][F] Bone Club : 50\r\nRemove 1 Bone Counter from this Pokémon in order to use this attack. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.'),
(10001, 71, 2, 'Hitmonlee', '[F][F] Double Kick : 30×\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.\r\n\r\n[F][F][C] Rolling Kick : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. '),
(10001, 72, 2, 'Hitmonchan', '[F] Mach Punch : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)'),
(10001, 73, 2, 'Rhydon', '[F] Mountain Break : 10\r\nDiscard the top 5 cards of your deck. If any of those cards are [F] Energy cards, put them into your hand.\r\n\r\n[F][F][F] One-Two Strike : 30+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage. '),
(10001, 74, 2, 'Kabuto', 'Pokémon Power : Fossilize\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, return all Evolution cards from 1 of your Pokémon in play that evolves from Mysterious Fossil to your hand. This power can''t be used if this Pokémon is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Razor Claw : 10+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage. '),
(10001, 75, 2, 'Aerodactyl', '[C] Supersonic :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Spiral Attack : 40\r\nThis Pokémon does 10 damage to itself. Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for the self-damage. '),
(10001, 76, 2, 'Abra', '[P] Psychic Beam :\r\nDoes 10 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. Don’t apply Weakness or Resistance. '),
(10001, 77, 2, 'Kadabra', '[P][P] Psycho Panic : 30\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon is Psychic, this attack''s base damage is doubled.\r\n\r\n[P][P][P] Blink : 30\r\nIf an attack damages this Pokémon during your opponent’s next turn, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)'),
(10001, 78, 2, 'Kadabra', '[P] Energy Restore :	\r\nPut a Special Energy card from your discard pile into your hand.\r\n\r\n[P][P] Energy Shock : 20\r\nIf your opponent attaches an Energy card to the Defending Pokémon during his or her next turn, that Pokémon becomes Paralyzed. '),
(10001, 79, 2, 'Alakazam', '[P][P] Psy-Panic : 30\r\nIf the Defending Pokémon is Psychic, this attack’s base damage is doubled.\r\n\r\n[P][P][P] Trans Damage :	\r\nDiscard all Energy cards attached to Alakazam. Move all damage counters from Alakazam to the Defending Pokémon. '),
(10001, 80, 2, 'Slowbro', '[P] Big Yawn :\r\nBoth the Defending Pokémon and this Pokémon are now Asleep.\r\n\r\n[P][P] Big Snore : 30\r\nYou can only use this attack if this Pokémon is Asleep. '),
(10001, 81, 2, 'Gastly', '[C] Frighten :\r\nYour opponent can''t play Trainer cards from his or her hand during his or her next turn.\r\n\r\n[P][C] Darkness : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. '),
(10001, 82, 2, 'Haunter', '[P] Poltergeist : 10×\r\nLook at your opponent''s hand. This attack does 10 damage times the number of Trainer cards your opponent has in his or her hand.\r\n\r\n[P][P] Bad Dreams : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. '),
(10001, 83, 2, 'Haunter', '[P] Eerie Light :	\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.\r\n\r\n[P][P] Grudge : 20+\r\nDoes 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken. '),
(10001, 84, 2, 'Gengar', 'Pokémon Power : Power of Darkness\r\nWhen you play Gengar from your hand, you may flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. Your opponent returns that Pokémon and all cards attached to it to his or her hand.\r\n\r\n[P][P][P] Psy Horror : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. '),
(10001, 85, 2, 'Hypno', 'Pokémon Power : Puppet Master\r\nIf a Clefairy Doll is your Active Pokémon, it may use any of this Pokémon''s attacks as long as this Pokémon has enough Energy cards attached to it to pay for that attack''s Energy cost. (The Clefairy Doll can make that attack even if it does not have the appropriate number or type of Energy attached to it necessary to make the attack.)\r\n\r\n[P][P] Mind Shock : 30\r\nThis attack''s damage isn''t affected by Weakness or Resistance. '),
(10001, 86, 2, 'Mr. Mime', 'Pokémon Power : Neutral Damage\r\nAs long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, each Active Pokémon has no Weakness or Resistance.\r\n\r\n[P][C] Juggling : 10×\r\nFlip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads. '),
(10001, 87, 2, 'Jynx', '[W] Ice Punch : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[W][W] Cold Breath : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. '),
(10001, 88, 2, 'Mewtwo', '[P] Psycho Crash : 10×\r\nDoes 10 damage times the total number of Psychic Energy cards attached to all of your opponent''s Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[P][P][C] Super Confusion : 50'),
(10001, 89, 2, 'Mewtwo', '[P][P] Complete Recovery :	\r\nDiscard all Energy cards attached to this Pokémon. Then, remove all damage counters and markers from this Pokémon and this Pokémon is no longer Poisoned or Confused.\r\n\r\n[P][P][C] Psycho Blast : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, discard 1 Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon. '),
(10001, 90, 2, 'Mewtwo', '[P] Energy Control :	\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, choose a basic Energy card attached to 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon and attach it to another of your opponent''s Pokémon of your choice.\r\n\r\n[P][P][P] Telekinesis :\r\nChoose 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)'),
(10001, 91, 2, 'Mew', '[C] Pound : 10\r\n\r\n[P] Psydupe :\r\nChoose an attack of 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon in play. Psydupe copies that attack. This attack does nothing if this Pokémon doesn''t have the Energy necessary to use that attack as well as the energy necessary to use Psydupe. (You must still do anything else required for that attack.) This Pokémon performs that attack. '),
(10001, 92, 2, 'Pidgey', '[C] Gust : 10\r\n\r\n[C][C] Quick Attack : 10+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage. '),
(10001, 93, 2, 'Pidgeotto', '[C][C] Twister : 20\r\nUnless this attack Knocks Out the Defending Pokémon, flip a coin. If heads, return all Trainer cards and Energy cards attached to the Defending Pokémon to your opponent''s hand.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Fly : 30\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent''s next turn. '),
(10001, 94, 2, 'Rattata', '[C] Scratch : 10\r\n\r\n[C] Tail Whip :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can''t attack during your opponent''s next turn. '),
(10001, 95, 2, 'Spearow', '[C] Fury Attack : 10×\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.\r\n\r\n[C] Gust : 10'),
(10001, 96, 2, 'Fearow', '[C][C] Quick Attack : 10+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Drill Dive : 50\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. '),
(10001, 97, 2, 'Clefairy', '[C] Follow Me :\r\nSwitch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Shining Fingers : 10\r\nThe Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. '),
(10001, 98, 2, 'Wigglytuff', 'Pokémon Power : Helping Hand\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, remove 1 Special Condition from your Active Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C][C] Expand : 20\r\nAll damage done to this Pokémon by attacks during your opponent''s next turn is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance.)'),
(10001, 99, 2, 'Doduo', '[C] Growl :\r\nDuring your opponent''s next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).\r\n\r\n[C][C] Peck : 20'),
(10001, 100, 2, 'Dodrio', '[C] Smash Kick : 20\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Tri Attack : 20×\r\nFlip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads. '),
(10001, 101, 2, 'Lickitung', '[C] Lick :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Stomp : 20+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage. '),
(10001, 102, 2, 'Chansey', '[C] Sing :\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Double Slap : 20×\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads. '),
(10001, 103, 2, 'Kangaskhan', '[C][C] Bite : 20\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Tail Drop : 80\r\nFlip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing. '),
(10001, 104, 2, 'Tauros', '[C][C] Kicking and Stamping : 20+\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage. If tails, your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon. '),
(10001, 105, 2, 'Ditto', 'Pokémon Power : Amazing Transformation\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, you may flip a coin. If heads, choose any Pokémon in play. From now on treat this Pokémon as if it were the same card as that Pokémon, including Hit Points, Weakness, and so on, except this Pokémon can’t evolve or devolve, always can use this Pokémon Power, and you may treat any Energy attached to Ditto as Energy of any type. If tails; if this Pokémon is Benched; if this Pokémon becomes Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed; or if the Pokémon you chose leaves play, treat this card as this Pokémon again. This power can’t be used if this Pokémon is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed. '),
(10001, 106, 2, 'Eevee', '[C] Gnaw : 10\r\n\r\n[C] Lunge : 20\r\nFlip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. '),
(10001, 107, 2, 'Porygon', '[C] 3D Attack : 10×\r\nFlip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Conversion 2 :\r\nChange this Pokémon Resistance to a type of your choice other than Colorless.'),
(10001, 108, 2, 'Snorlax', 'Pokémon Power : Guard\r\nAs long as Snorlax is your Active Pokémon, the Defending Pokémon can''t Retreat. This power stops working when Snorlax is affected by a Special Condition.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C][C] Roll Over : 30\r\nSnorlax is now Asleep. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.'),
(10001, 109, 2, 'Flash', 'Each player looks at the top 5 cards of his or her deck. Your opponent rearranges his or her 5 cards as he or she likes and puts them on top of his of her deck face up. Then, you rearrange your 5 cards as you like and put them on top of your deck face up. (If a player shuffles his or her deck when it still has face up cards in it, that player puts them face down again before shuffling.)'),
(10001, 110, 2, 'Fossil Excavation', 'You may search your deck for a Mysterious Fossil or choose 1 Mysterious Fossil in your discard pile. Show that card to your opponent and put it into your hand. Either way, shuffle your deck afterward. '),
(10001, 111, 2, 'Guard Spec', 'Attach Guard Spec to 1 of your Pokémon in play. At the end of your opponent''s turn, discard Guard Spec. Prevent all effects of attacks, except damage, done to the Pokémon Guard Spec is attached to. '),
(10001, 112, 2, 'Master Ball', 'Look at 7 cards from the top of your deck. You may choose a Basic Pokémon or Evolution card from those cards, show it your opponent, then put it into your hand. Shuffle the rest into your deck. '),
(10001, 113, 2, 'Max Revive', 'Discard 2 Energy cards from your hand in order to put 1 Basic Pokémon from your discard pile onto your Bench. (You can''t play Max Revive if your Bench is full.)'),
(10001, 114, 2, 'Moon Stone', 'You may search your deck for a Colorless Evolution card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. '),
(10001, 115, 2, 'Pokémon Retransfer', 'Put an Evolution card from your discard pile on top of your deck.'),
(10001, 116, 2, 'Pokémon Tower', 'This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play. If another card with the same name is in play, you can''t play this card.\r\n\r\nIf the effect of a Pokémon Power, attack, Energy card, or Trainer card would put a card in a discard pile into its owner''s hand, that card stay in that discard pile instead.'),
(10001, 117, 2, 'Bill''s PC', 'This card is needed to exchange either an Omanyte, Haunter, Machoke, Graveler, or Kadabra for its corresponding evolution card.\r\n\r\nThis is a card necessary for enlistment in the &quot;Communication Evolution campaign&quot;. For detailed contents, carefully read the remarks on the &quot;Expansion Sheet – Green Edition&quot;.'),
(10001, 118, 2, 'Imakuni''s PC', 'Imakuni? has a PC too. On days off he gets inside it and remembers all sorts of memories.\r\n\r\nI''m doing &quot;Imakuni?''s Evolution Campaign&quot; all by myself. But no matter what I do I can''t evolve.'),
(10001, 119, 2, 'Imakuni''s Nasty Plot', 'When you play this card, you may remove damage counters when your opponent isn''t looking. And no matter what they ask, pretend you don''t know about it.\r\n\r\nThis is the new red and even more polished Imakuni?. If you happen to see Imakuni? in the streets, always say &quot;You look thinner than you do on TV.&quot;'),
(10001, 120, 2, 'Ooyama''s Pikachu', '[C] Greetings : 10 (more or less)\r\nBe polite but attack when your opponent is in an unguarded moment.\r\n\r\n[L][L] Pretend Show : 30\r\nPretend to be asleep but attack when your opponent is in an unguarded moment. (Sneaky of you.)'),
(10001, 121, 2, '4 Prize Battle', 'This is a rule by which each player puts out 4 prize cards to battle when he or she would put out 6 prize cards to battle. The player who Knocks Out 4 of his or her opponent''s Pokémon and draws all 4 prize cards wins.\r\n\r\nThese rules have been used in official tournaments. Try playing when you are short on time, such as during break time at school, etc.!'),
(10001, 122, 2, '20 Damage from Confusion', 'This is a simple rule for when a Pokémon uses an attack while it is Confused and the coin flip was tails (when the Pokémon was Confused). Regardless of the type of attack, the Pokémon that used the attack itself receives 20 damage.\r\n\r\nPokémon card rules recommended for beginners. Official tournaments have since adopted this rule.'),
(10001, 123, 2, '3 Deck Battle', 'Each battling player readies 3 decks with different contents. Next, they put their decks face down in play and decide the order of the decks with which they will battle. Also, they start battling with the decks 1 time each in the decided order. The player who won twice in the end wins. '),
(10001, 124, 2, 'Dugtrio Team Battle', 'Three people form a team, each bringing decks with different contents, and battle team vs. team. Each team decides the order its members will battle in, and the battles begin, 1 on 1. When all 3 persons'' battles are over, the team that won twice wins.'),
(10001, 125, 2, 'Deck Exchange', 'Each player brings a deck and battles 3 times. They battle the first time with their deck, the second time they exchange decks, and the third time with their decks once more. A player gets 1 point each time he or she won with his or her deck and 2 points when he or she won with his or her opponent''s deck. With the results of the 3 battles, the player with the higher total number of points wins. '),
(64, 1, 2, 'Team Magma''s Numel', '[R][C] Ember : 30\r\nDiscard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.'),
(64, 2, 2, 'Team Magma''s Camerupt', 'Ability : Burning Draft\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a [F] or [R] Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[R][C][C] Flame Ball : 60\r\nMove a basic Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.'),
(64, 3, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Spheal', '[W] Water Gun : 10'),
(64, 4, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Sealeo', '[W][C] Splatter :\r\nThis attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)\r\n\r\n[W][C][C] Hail Storm : 60+\r\nIf your opponent''s Active Pokémon is a Team Magma Pokémon, this attack does 60 more damage.'),
(64, 5, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Walrein', '[C] Power Blow : 30×\r\nThis attack does 30 damage times the amount of Energy attached to this Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[W][W][W][C] Dual Blizzard :\r\nDiscard 2 [W] Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 80 damage to 2 of your opponent''s Pokémon. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)'),
(64, 6, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Kyogre-EX', 'Pokémon-EX rule : When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\nAbility : Power Saver\r\nIf there are 4 or fewer Team Aqua Pokémon in play, this Pokémon can''t attack.\r\n\r\n[W][W][W][C] Aqua Impact : 80+\r\nThis attack does 20 more damage for each [C] in your opponent''s Active Pokémon''s Retreat Cost.'),
(64, 7, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Grimer', '[P] Pound : 10\r\n\r\n[P][C][C] Mud-Slap : 30'),
(64, 8, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Muk', 'Ability : Sludge Festival\r\nThe Retreat Cost of each Pokémon in play (except for Team Aqua Pokémon) is [C] more.\r\n\r\n[P][C][C] Pester : 60+\r\nIf your opponent''s Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 60 more damage.'),
(64, 9, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Seviper', '[P] Venomous Fang : 10\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, your opponent''s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.\r\n\r\n[C][C] Venom Tail : 30\r\nIf your opponent''s Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, discard an Energy attached to that Pokémon.'),
(64, 10, 2, 'Team Magma''s Baltoy', '[P][C] Telekinesis :\r\nThis attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon. This attack''s damage isn''t affected by Weakness or Resistance.'),
(64, 11, 2, 'Team Magma''s Claydol', 'Ability : Magma Switch\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may move a basic Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to 1 of your Team Magma Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[P][C][C] Power Beam : 70'),
(64, 12, 2, 'Team Magma''s Aron', '[F] Gnaw : 10'),
(64, 13, 2, 'Team Magma''s Lairon', '[F][C] Gnaw : 30\r\n\r\n[F][C][C] Take Down : 60\r\nThis Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.'),
(64, 14, 2, 'Team Magma''s Aggron', '[F][C] Rock Stomp : 40×\r\nDiscard as many [F] Energy attached to your Pokémon as you like. This attack does 40 damage times the amount of [F] Energy you discarded.\r\n\r\n[F][F][F][C] Boulder Storm : 120\r\nThis attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent''s Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it. (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)'),
(64, 15, 2, 'Team Magma''s Groudon-EX', 'Pokémon-EX rule : When a Pokémon-EX has been Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.\r\n\r\nAbility : Power Saver\r\nIf there are 4 or fewer Team Magma Pokémon in play, this Pokémon can''t attack.\r\n\r\n[F][F][F][C] Magma Quake : 80+\r\nIf your opponent''s Active Pokémon already has damage counters on it, this attack does 80 more damage.'),
(64, 16, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Poochyena', '[C] Roar : Your opponent switches his or her Active Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.\r\n\r\n[W][C] Bite : 20');
INSERT INTO `cards_names` (`set_id`, `number`, `local_language_id`, `name`, `text`) VALUES
(64, 17, 2, 'Team Magma''s Poochyena', '[C] Infiltrate : Your opponent reveals his or her hand.\r\n\r\n[F][C] Bite : 20'),
(64, 18, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Mightyena', '[W][C] Teampact : 30×\r\nFlip a coin for each Team Aqua Pokémon you have in play. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.\r\n\r\n[W][W][C] Crunch : 80\r\nFlip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to your opponent''s Active Pokémon.'),
(64, 19, 2, 'Team Magma''s Mightyena', '[F][C] Bite : 30\r\n\r\n[F][F][C] Hostile Fang : 80\r\nIf your opponent''s Active Pokémon is a Team Aqua Pokémon, this attack does 40 more damage.'),
(64, 20, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Carvanha', '[D] Fin Smack : 10×\r\nFlip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.'),
(64, 21, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Sharpedo', 'Ability : Aqua Search\r\nOnce during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Team Aqua Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.\r\n\r\n[D][C][C] Sharp Fang : 70'),
(64, 22, 2, 'Team Magma''s Zangoose', '[C] Call for Family :\r\nSearch your deck for up to 2 Basic Team Magma Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.\r\n\r\n[C][C][C] Team Play : 20×\r\nThis attack does 20 damage times the number of Team Magma Pokémon on your Bench.'),
(64, 23, 2, 'Aqua Diffuser', 'Attach a Pokémon Tool to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn''t already have a Pokémon Tool attached to it.\r\n\r\nThe Team Aqua Pokémon this card is attached to can also use the attack on this card. (You still need the necessary Energy to use this attack.)\r\n\r\n[W] Aqua Diffuser :\r\nYour opponent''s Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.'),
(64, 24, 2, 'Magma Pointer', 'Attach a Pokémon Tool to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn''t already have a Pokémon Tool attached to it.\r\n\r\nThe Team Magma Pokémon this card is attached to can also use the attack on this card. (You still need the necessary Energy to use this attack.)\r\n\r\n[F] Magma Pointer :\r\nThis attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent''s Pokémon (Don''t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)'),
(64, 25, 2, 'Team Aqua Admin', 'You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).\r\n\r\nAttach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to your Active Team Aqua Pokémon.'),
(64, 26, 2, 'Team Aqua Grunt', 'You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).\r\n\r\nDiscard a card from your hand. (If you can''t discard a card, you can''t play this card.) Draw 3 cards. If you discarded a Team Aqua Pokémon, draw 1 more card.'),
(64, 27, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Great Ball', 'Search you deck for a Basic Team Aqua Pokémon and a basic [W] Energy card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.'),
(64, 28, 2, 'Team Aqua''s Secret Base', 'This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play. If another card with the same name is in play, you can''t play this card.\r\n\r\nThe Retreat Cost of each Pokémon in play (except for Team Aqua Pokémon) is [C] more.'),
(64, 29, 2, 'Team Magma Admin', 'You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).\r\n\r\nPut up to 3 Team Magma Pokémon from your discard pile into your hand.'),
(64, 30, 2, 'Team Magma Grunt', 'You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).\r\n\r\nDiscard a card from your hand. (If you can''t discard a card, you can''t play this card.) Draw 3 cards. If you discarded a Team Magma Pokémon, draw 1 more card.'),
(64, 31, 2, 'Team Magma''s Great Ball', 'Search you deck for a Basic Team Magma Pokémon and a basic [F] Energy card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.'),
